description.plain:
Arizona Zervas, or as some call him, AZ, is a rapper, singer, songwriter, and producer from Maryland. Arizona released his first song in 11th grade while attending high school in Maryland. After his first release, Arizona’s music quickly spread across the web and within months became a known name in the underground music scene.

In 2019, Arizona found even more success when his song “ROXANNE” became viral on the social media app TikTok. The song peaked at #4 on the Billboard Hot 100.

In 2022 Arizona’s Hit “FML” become certified Platinum Selling Over 1 Million units in the U.S. alone.

With no major label, AZ has acquired a die hard following. He Has reached over 2 Billion streams. He is most known for his versatile style and melodic lyrics, and with each new release, Arizona Zervas is quickly showing the world why he deserves to be next up.

songs.title: ROXANNE

description.plain:
“Roxanne” is a 2019 single by Arizona Zervas. It started gaining traction on the popular app TikTok in October of 2019. “Roxanne” is the most popular song by Arizona Zervas to date.

“Roxanne” is a song that describes a girl called Roxanne, who, according to Arizona, likes to party and spend her dad’s money. It describes his relationship with her and just in general, how she acts and is.

Arizona Zervas said this about the song:

“Roxanne” is a song about a girl I wanted but didn’t need.
